<h2>OPD Investigation Appointment</h2><hr />
<span class="title">Screen Overview </span><br />
<div class="clear"></div>
This screen captures the OPD Patient investigation Appointments for the out patient. This screen will be used for maintaining Patient  investigation appointments information for all clinical departments. This screen will contain information of Investigation name, time Slot, Slots Available, HIN, Patient Name, Service no ,Patient Name, Age, Sex
<br /><hr /><br />

<img src="images/app_opdinvestigationappoint.jpg" width="725"  /><br /><br />
<hr />
<p>
<span class="title">Department:</span><br />
User can select the department from the given list, this will come from department screen, it can't remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">Investigation Date:  </span> 
    <br />User can select Appointment date based on Department  based all department time slots will display, it can't remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">Equipment:  </span> 
    <br />Based on user selection Department the equipment list will display, it can't remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">Slots Available:  </span> 
    <br />Based on Department and Appointment date all slots will display it can't remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title">Appointment Criteria: </span> 
    <br />Appointment Criteria contains 2 types 1) Service No 2) HIN No 
          Service No: If user knows service no then all service details will fetch automatically from the data base.
          HIN No: If user knows HIN No then all service details will fetch automatically from the data base.
<br />
    <span class="title">Service No:</span> 
    <br />User can write service No Based on service No  the Patient details will display.
          Patient details like Service Person Name, HIN No, Patient Name, Mobile No, Sex, Age, Doctorâ€™s Name.
<br />
    <span class="title">Submit (Button):</span> 
    <br />	By clicking on Submit button user can save the data. 
<br />
    <span class="title">Reset (Button):</span> 
    <br />	Clicking on reset button, will clear the current or existing data.


</p>
